anacron
****************************************
anacronjob is similar to crontab but it simple difference crontab is works only when is system is powered on , anacron is works when system was powred off ,it can be do the job sheduled time when the system was off 

>ancron is placed at the location is 
   cat /etc/anacrontab

>Here three commands located in this location 
  1)    /etc/cron.daily
  2)   /etc/cron.weekly
  3)  /etc/cron.monthly   

>cron.daily is a folder here we place a script it will run once perday
it runs every day after 5 minutes when the system reboot
   example:
   create a one anacron job
   got to cd /etc/cron.daily
   vim anacron-job
   write the script like this
      #!/bin/bash
      echo "hello world" >> /tmp/ancron-test.txt
      save and exit 

   if you run the job forcefully by using this command :anacron -f

    give the permissions 
     chmod +x /etc/cron.daily/anacron-job

  check the job location 
     cat /tmp/anacron-test.txt

  run-parts the script
  run-parts means runs all scripts inside a directory one by one

     run-parts /etc/cron.daily/anacron-job      

>cron.weekly:cron.weekly is runs weekly after 25 minutes when the system reboot
      
   /etc/cron.weekly:it is a one directory inside the directory we create a jobs

   example :
    create a one job 
      vim weekly.job

   inside the weekly.job
     #!/bin/bash
     /usr/bin/yum update -y >> /var/log/weekly-test.job

   <save and exit>

   give the permissions 
     chmod +x /etc/anacron/cron.weekly/weekly.job
    
    run parts the cron.weekly

     run-parts /etc/cron.weekly

>cron.monthly:runs the job monthly after 45 minutes when the system reboot     

